}`,
        output: topic.includes('OOP') || topic.includes('Polymorphism')
          ? `Rex says: Woof!
Luna says: Meow!
Buddy says: Woof!`
          : topic.includes('Linked') ? `10 -> 20 -> 30` : `Demonstrating ${topic}`,
        explanation: `This example shows the fundamental ${topic} pattern. Notice how the code follows the syntax_reference above. Run it yourself and trace the execution manually using the step_by_step_guide.`
      },
      example_2: {
        title: `Real-World ${topic} Use`,
        description: `Shows how ${topic} appears in practical Java applications.`,
        code: topic.includes('OOP') || topic.includes('Polymorphism')
          ? `public class ShapeCalculator {
